Section: web
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Polycom Open Firmware <noreply@github.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/Polycom-Open-Firmware/chromium-a53

Package: op-app-chromium
Architecture: all
Depends: chromium (>= 150), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Chromium kiosk app for Polycom TC8 (hardware-acceleration defaults)
 Ships /etc/chromium.d defaults that switch Debian's chromium (built by
 the chromium-a53 recipe) into its hardware-accelerated configuration on
 the Polycom TC8 panel: native Wayland (cage compositor), etnaviv GPU
 rasterization, and V4L2 stateless video decode on the Hantro VPU.
 .
 Pull this package in from a profile metapackage (op-tc8-profile-*) once
 the Chromium kiosk stack replaces cog/WPE.
